data.name: GabiteTalk
data.value: Eh? What're you giving me that look for? Is it 'cause I'm blue? Look, I've been like this my entire life! Apparently there's a name for it too: I'm allegedly one of those so-called "shinies" who show up every now and then. Shininess is supposed to be a really uncommon trait and I've been told it's good luck to see one. If only said "good luck" applied to me as well - then I wouldn't be stuck all the way down here sandwiched between those perplexing dungeons!

data.name: GlimmoraTalk
data.value: Hark this, outsider. Beyond this place lies another road that leads to no other road. The secret is not there but there before. Many another false path exists, for not all roads within the Yendorian Road lead to directly Yendor.

data.name: CarbinkTalk
data.value: Oh, an adventurer traveling the road to Yendor? I shell tell you of a secret that has been passed down in this area. The people of Yendor happened upon a high tower, constructed upon the ceiling of the road. Upon breaching into it, a mysterious object laid bare. They took the object from its pedestal and felt a grand quake, and upon the surface a trinity of grand towers had vanished. It is written that should the object be returned to its rightful place, the three towers shall return to challenge the one who brought them back to the surface.
data.comment: Carbink brings up the Inverted Tower
